    "architect": "Aldo van Eyck",
    "year": 1966,
    "location": "Sonsbeek Park, Arnhem, Netherlands",
    "description": "Temporary exhibition pavilion. A field of parallel masonry walls with semicircular connecting segments and circular concrete disc screens, arranged within a circular ground plane. The spatial composition creates a labyrinthine sequence of intimate rooms and passages.",
